executor_description: A client syncs content by using the sync endpoint. A single sync consists of one or more pages, each a separate request and response.  The first time a client synchronizes content it sends a request to the sync endpoint with the URI query parameter initial set to true.  You should only sync with initial=true for the initial sync when a client has no existing content. This transfers all content from a space, but does not contain content deleted from fields or deleted assets and content entries.  The limit parameter sets the page size for the number of retrieved entries. The limit is useful when you have very large content entries and reach the maximum response size limit. This limit is then encoded in the synchronization token and used for all following synchronizations.  Sync only contains content from the master environment and is not containing deltas from sandbox environments.

executor_description: Synchronization responses contain either a nextPageUrl or nextSyncUrl attribute. If there is more content for the current sync, nextPageUrl will contain an URL with a sync_token which will retrieve the next page. This continues until you have retrieved all content.  At this point, the response will contain a nextSyncUrl which you use to make requests in the future and retrieve delta updates between the current content on Contentful and what you retrieved with your last sync request. Upon completion, you will receive a new nextSyncUrl which you can again use for future updates.  If a client loses the nextSyncUrl, the client should delete its local content and perform an initial synchronization again.
